ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported
0= Normal; 1=Abnormal, not clinically significant; 2=Abnormal, clinically significant

1 = Constitutional symptoms (e.g., fever, weight loss); 2 = Eyes; 3 = Ears, Nose, Mouth, Throat; 4 = Cardiovascular; 5 = Respiratory; 6 = Abdominal/GI; 7 = Musculoskeletal; 8 = Skin; 9 = Neurological/CNS; 10 = Psychiatric; 11 = Endocrine; 12 = Blood/ Hematology/ Lymphatic; 13 = Immunological/Allergy; 14 = Gynecological/Urological/Renal; 15 = Other, specify
The date the investigator instructed the subject to start the new dose of study drug or placebo.

ElementDescription: What is the highest tolerated dose the subject was able to achieve and maintain during the titration period?
Study drug. Date hold started MM/DD/YYYY
Has subject engaged in Non-Suicidal Self-Injurious Behavior? Since Last Visit. PX640107_NonSuicidal_SelfInjurious_Behavior_SinceLastVisit
